"""
shap_explainer.py
=================
SHAP-based explainability pipeline for the hybrid fraud detection framework.

Paper
-----
"A Hybrid Deep Learning and Explainable AI Framework for Real-Time
Financial Fraud Detection in Dynamic Environments"

Role in the hybrid pipeline
----------------------------
This module sits downstream of Stage 2 (ensemble.py) and wraps the
fitted XGBoost/LightGBM head with TreeSHAP to produce two kinds of
explanation artifact for every scored transaction:

    Global explanations  — which embedding dimensions (and, by proxy,
        which raw input features) drive fraud predictions across the
        full validation set.  Used for model auditing and regulatory
        reporting.

    Local explanations   — per-transaction additive decomposition
        phi_0 + sum_i phi_i(x) = F(x), giving auditors a reason code
        for every individual alert.

Paper references
----------------
"For each decision, SHAP produces an additive explanation:
 p_hat(x) = sigma(phi_0 + sum_{i=1}^{d} phi_i(x))
 where phi_i is the Shapley contribution of feature i relative to a
 background baseline phi_0."  (System Model section)

"Every prediction of the hybrid was accompanied by a SHAP-based
additive explanation, which was obtained with the help of the TreeSHAP
algorithm with global feature ranking and transaction-specific
explanations."  (Experimental Datasets section)

"The global SHAP rankers are always more stable around elements that
can be termed as domain intuition such as amount of transactions,
bursts of transactions, and device reuse between accounts."
(Results Discussion section)

"Rank correlation coefficients in the range of 0.8 to 0.9 indicate
that it is not an illusion of the sampling but an overall description
of what the model is all about in its logic."  (Results Discussion)

Lemma 2 (paper) — alignment of SHAP with the cost-optimal threshold
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The fraud decision delta*(x) at threshold tau* is equivalent to a
linear inequality in SHAP space:

    sum_i phi_i(x)  >=  log(tau* / (1 - tau*)) - phi_0

This means every audit query "why was this transaction flagged?" has a
clean additive answer grounded in the cost model.

Usage
-----
    from src.shap_explainer import FraudSHAPExplainer

    # Build explainer from a fitted ensemble head
    explainer = FraudSHAPExplainer(
        ensemble_head=head,
        feature_names=feature_cols,   # original input feature names
        embedding_dim=32,
    )
    explainer.fit(Z_background)       # Z from training embeddings

    # Global importance (Table-style + figures)
    global_imp = explainer.global_importance(Z_val)
    explainer.plot_global_bar(global_imp, save_path="results/figures/shap_global.png")
    explainer.plot_beeswarm(Z_val, save_path="results/figures/shap_beeswarm.png")

    # Local explanation for one transaction
    record = explainer.explain_transaction(Z_single, fraud_score=0.97)
    explainer.plot_waterfall(record, save_path="results/figures/shap_waterfall.png")

    # Stability across folds (paper reports Spearman r = 0.8–0.9)
    stability = explainer.cross_fold_stability(rankings_per_fold)

    # Inference-time explanation artifact (for FastAPI / audit log)
    artifact = explainer.explanation_artifact(Z_single, transaction_id="TX_001")
"""

